column2: There’s no way we are going to see this movie if Amber Heard is in it. No one I know will be attending if she’s in it.
column34:
There is a petition going to drop Amber Heard from Aquaman 2 with over 4 million signatures but Warner Bros released a statement stating they will not give into fan pressure and drop Ms Heard from the film. This shows how much they care about the average movie goer when their profits are directly linked to these average movie goers. 
Johnny Depp was labelled guilty until proven innocent with just AH’s allegations and dropped by WB so now when AH’s reality is coming forward with evidence and recordings they refuse to drop her and that is not fair. 
I believe if the same 4 million people decide to Boycott Aquaman 2, with the average adult ticket price of $13.69, 4 million people refusing to watch the movie could cost them almost $55,000,000. They say they won’t be swayed by “peer pressure,” but what about 55 million dollars? 

Abusers should be treatedly equally, men and women. Just because JD was a man he was treated so badly, he wasn’t even proven guilty all of those were just allegations at that point and he was dropped from such big movies like Fantastic Beasts and Pirates of the Carribean but Amber Heard gets to still play her role in Aquaman 2 after all she has done?

Justice should be served. Amber Heard should also face the consequences of her actions.

column2: If this was a man who had been behind such heinous abuse and lies used to destroy lives he would have been dropped immediately.  Johnny depp is actually the perfect example as he was dropped by all of Hollywood essentially. He remained black balled for 6 years as guilty until proven innocent.  What message do we as women send when asking for equal rights,treatment, and social standing in society as well as in requests for justice during our own abuse trials. If we allow her to destroy lives, warp abuse movements to further her public image and Career with false/borrowed rape stories, and obliterate the truth with her multitude of lies then we may as well change our request for equality to a request for women's superiority to men. She spent 6 years ripping away at a man's life with lies causing immense emotional and psychological damage, to not only Johnny but his entire family,  after previously suffering her physical abuse for years on end. He had no choice or control of his career and/or life as he sat watching the empire he built as a kind gentle man and amazingly talented actor slip away being let go from film after film After film. Yet she gets to stay because?...why? She's only in the film 10 minutes? SOOO! Replace her. She created this lie to further her career at the cost of others suffering.  We all know now the truth about this wannabe actress and I believe its time she pays the piper. Ill finish by saying this....the devil and all of his evils truly are wrapped in beautiful packaging. A  Beauty with a black soul. This movie and all who worked so hard should not have to pay the price of a mass boycott to save the part of a C list actress who cares for no one else in this world but herself.  She does not deserve nor has she earned anyone's support

I am sure most of us want to enjoy Aquaman [Jason Mamoa] and have her face on the screen as a constant reminder of that trial.
